{"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Core-Functionality","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Tracking","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/URLSchemeConfiguring","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/AnchoredTooltips","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/PushNotifications","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues"],"title":"Core Functionality","generated":true}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit"],["doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"In order to target content to the right users at the right time, you need to identify users and send Appcues data about them.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Identifying","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/appcueskit\/identifying"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"AppcuesKit"}],"role":"article","title":"Identifying and Managing Users","roleHeading":"Article"},"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Identifying-Known-Users","text":"Identifying Known Users"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Appcues recommends choosing opaque and hard to guess user IDs, such as a UUID. See the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.appcues.com\/article\/159-faq#choosing-a-user-id"},{"type":"text","text":" for more details about how to choose a User ID."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/identify(userID:properties:)","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is recommended that the application identify a user at moments such as sign in, and also when the app starts up on a cold launch with existing log in credentials. This will ensure that any user properties tied to this user can be kept accurately up to date."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The inverse of identifying is resetting. For example, if a user logs out of your app. Calling "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/reset()","type":"reference"},{"text":" will disable tracking of screens and events until a user is identified again.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you have special security needs and your account has been configured to use the Appcues identity verification feature, follow the steps outlined in the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/docs.appcues.com\/dev-installing-appcues\/identity-verification","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", when calling "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/identify(userID:properties:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Identifying-Anonymous-Users","level":2,"text":"Identifying Anonymous Users"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/anonymous()","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The format of anonymous IDs can customized with "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/Config\/anonymousIDFactory(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":". Anonymous IDs will always be prefixed with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"anon:"},{"type":"text","text":" by the SDK."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Grouping-Users","level":2,"text":"Grouping Users"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Associating a user with a group allows you to additionally capture analytics at the group level, and target content to show based upon group membership and properties."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/group(groupID:properties:)","type":"reference"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To ensure the most accurate content targeting based upon group information, it’s recommended to supply the group information immediately after a new user is identified.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://com.appcues.sdk/documentation/AppcuesKit/GettingStarted":{"url":"\/documentation\/appcueskit\/gettingstarted","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/GettingStarted","type":"topic","title":"Getting Started with Appcues iOS SDK","role":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Initialize the SDK and track events.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article"},"doc://com.appcues.sdk/documentation/AppcuesKit/URLSchemeConfiguring":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/appcueskit\/urlschemeconfiguring","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/URLSchemeConfiguring","abstract":[{"text":"The Appcues iOS SDK includes support for a custom URL scheme that supports previewing Appcues experiences in-app prior to publishing and launching the Appcues debugger.","type":"text"}],"role":"article","type":"topic","title":"Configuring the Appcues URL Scheme"},"doc://com.appcues.sdk/documentation/AppcuesKit/Appcues/identify(userID:properties:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/appcueskit\/appcues\/identify(userid:properties:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"identify","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"userID","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"St